---
alwaysApply: true
---

Before making any code change, do full impact analysis.

Rules for every change:
- Do not make isolated edits.
- First understand the current behavior, the business logic, and all dependencies.
- Trace the full impact of the requested change across:
  - all callers/usages
  - related pages
  - includes/partials
  - forms
  - API handlers / backend actions
  - database queries
  - calculations / totals / balances
  - filters / search / status logic
  - exports / PDF / Excel / print views
  - notifications
  - permissions / role visibility
  - customer-facing vs internal-facing views
  - legacy pages and duplicate flows
- After changing anything, update every affected area so the system stays consistent.
- Do not mark the task complete if only the direct function/page was edited.
- Verify downstream effects, edge cases, and compatibility with existing data.
- If a change affects statuses, quantities, prices, totals, or workflow logic, re-check all dependent calculations and UI states.
- If a change affects a field, function, or status, search for all references and also inspect indirect usage, not only exact text matches.
- Prefer safe and consistent architecture over quick patches.
- At the end, report:
  1. what was changed
  2. what other files/pages/functions were impacted
  3. what was updated because of the impact
  4. any risks or manual QA still needed
